## Workflow Format V2 (Adaptive)

If a workflow.yaml contains `sections:` instead of `steps:`, use the adaptive format:
- Read the `briefing:` for global instructions
- Each section has `id`, `name`, `required`, `hints`, and `interaction_types`
- Fill sections through natural conversation -- don't follow a rigid order
- Use the interaction type mappings from workflow-instructions.md
- Mark sections complete as you go
- Save progress to the document output path after each section

## Claude Code-Specific

### Skills
Skills are in `~/.unreal-companion/skills/` (BMGD skills) and `~/.claude/skills/` (Claude Code skills).

### Resolution Order

When looking for workflows, agents, or skills:
1. `.unreal-companion/` (project-level overrides)
2. `~/.unreal-companion/custom/` (user customizations)
3. `~/.unreal-companion/defaults/` (installed defaults)

### Agent Personas

Load the agent persona from `~/.unreal-companion/agents/defaults/{agent-id}/agent.md` and adopt their communication style, expressions, and expertise.
